Pelvic fin moderately long; distal margin apparently nearly straight, with first ray longest. Pelvic-fin insertion apparently located anterior to middle of SL and posterior of vertical through posterior terminus of base of dorsal fin (
Fig. 24
). Tip of adpressed pelvic fin extending beyond middle of SL and to beyond anterior limit of vent but falling short of anal-fin origin. Medial most pelvic-fin ray with membranous attachment to body along basal two-thirds of its length.

Pectoral-fin length approximately two-thirds of HL. Pectoral-fin margin very gently convex, with first ray longest. First pectoral-fin ray not spinous and without distal filament (see also 
Fig. 24
).
